content.description:
This is a second pitch extension that puts you at the top of the wall. Climb one of the routes to the left of the large, left-facing dihedral, and continue past the clean panel on your right (

The Pony

). Pass another set of anchors, and climb the rightmost slab route to the top of the wall. Gear is required depending on how you piece your line together. With a 70m rope, you can climb to the top from the ground, do one lower out, and then lower all the way. Watch the ends of your rope!!!
